name: All-Campus Healthcare Symposium
description: Join UW HOSA at the 19th annual All-Campus Healthcare Symposium! This networking event provides healthcare career-seeking students an opportunity to hear from a variety of professionals working in various areas. The event features a keynote speaker who works in healthcare, often a medical doctor pursuing groundbreaking research, as well as a variety of other healthcare students and professionals. Following the keynote speaker we will break out into multiple sessions featuring different healthcare fields for students to get an opportunity to ask questions in a Q&A panel style manner. There will be a breakout room for pre-med, pre-pa, nursing, as well as students interested in physical or occupational therapy. The goal of the event is to provide students with an opportunity to network with professionals in their desired fields and learn about a variety of healthcare careers! All UW students are welcome! Food will be provided!

name: Let's Talk (International Student Focus)
description:
Mental Health Services and ISS Present: Let's Talk (International Student focus)
No-cost, informal, confidential consultations on campus and virtually
No topic is off limits and going to Let’s Talk  can help you gain insight, support, and information about other resources.
Common concerns include: stress, sadness, worry, relationships, academics, family problems, and financial struggles.
Let’s Talk is not a substitute for ongoing counseling and doesn’t constitute mental health treatment, but consultants can listen to specific problems, help explore solutions, and introduce you to what it’s like to speak to a member of our staff.

name: Thanksgiving Connection Banquet
description: The Thanksgiving Connection banquet is a collaborative event designed to bring together international, domestic students, and UW faculty. The event aims to foster cultural exchange, community building, and professional connections among students, faculty, and professionals involved in East Asian studies and international programs at UW-Madison. Taking place on November 22 at Gordon’s Symphony Hall, the banquet will feature speeches from organizational leaders and sponsors, including CLACC, WISMA, the Center for East Asian Studies (CEAS), and potentially International Student Services (ISS), and more. These speeches could help raise awareness about other RSO-affiliated organizations, introduce speakers, and provide valuable insights into East Asian related programs and opportunities. Attendees will have the opportunity to network, enjoy authentic Asian cuisine food, and participate in various social activities such as Chinese board games (Mahjong, Doudizhu, Xiangqi, etc.), calligraphy, interactive table discussions, charades, and many more! The event's goals are to celebrate and promote cultural diversity, provide students with an opportunity to connect with faculty and advisors in a relaxed environment, the opportunity to connect international students and students from the U.S., and strengthen the ties between various student organizations on campus. With a projected attendance of 100 guests, the banquet also serves as a platform for recognizing the contributions of volunteers, TAs, and professors who support the growth of language and cultural studies at UW-Madison.
date_time: Friday, November 22 2024 at 6:00 PM CST to Friday, November 22 2024 at 9:00 PM CST
